<br>
Even that isn't always successful, as was proven when someone jumped on a corpse and ninja'd an item off of it, as it was being released for the person who was really supposed to get it.  So, you usually also have to patrol the area, doing /tells and /shouts for everyone else to back away from the corpse.<br>
<br>
If a person ninja's by &quot;accident&quot;, then they should be willing to do one of two things...<br>
1) wait around for a GM to move the item<br>
2) offer something of equal or greater value, to make up for what they stole (yes, stole).<br>
<br>
Next time, I would also take this to an officer of that person's guild (assuming they are guilded, which they may not be).  Sometimes, if the person isn't upstanding, the guild will put pressure on them to make things right.  Most guilds don't want people with that kind of rep around.  Looks bad for the guild.<br>
<br>
Sorry you had to go through this.  It's very frustrating.<br>
